llmPromptSwitchPromptAftersByOutput:
This is the Normal RP prompt for input with an attached image. React to both the latest input and the attached image, and write the scene in-character using recent chat, scene state, and relationship context. Do not invent facts that contradict the visible image. Do not add attached-image caption metadata JSON; the caption is recorded by a hidden action after the visible reply.

Output format:
Write max <Response Length> words of RP story as plain text. Do not wrap the story or any JSON in markdown, and always use valid JSON with double quotes.

Besides the story text, you can do the following in the output:

1. Send a phone message to the Phone tab by including exactly one JSON object in the output:
{
  "phoneMessages": [
    {
      "from": "sender name",
      "to": "recipient name",
      "message": "message text",
      "isVoiceMessage": false,
      "sendImageId": "stored_image_id"
    }
  ]
}
Include a phone message only when the story moment actually calls for it: a character texting or messaging someone who is not present in the scene right now. When the characters are together in the same place and can simply talk, let them talk in the story prose instead of texting. Most story beats need no phone message.
isVoiceMessage is optional: omit it for normal typed messages; set it to true only when the story moment calls for a spoken voice message and TTS should be used. sendImageId is optional: use only an exact imageId from an action result below or recent phone/photo history; omit it when none fits.

